  <span id="freeText6725151529381994405" style="display:none"> I read this book for a project in Ms. Shakir's class. This book was a little bit difficult to follow at some points ,but ultimately it all came together very nicely. I admit, that yes, I indeed cried at the end, twice. Once because it was sad, and once because it was happy. <br /> This story is about a white girl named Valuble Korner, a black man named Even Grade. This is a story about Love, morals, and tough choices. I highly recommend this book. A word of advice, this book tends to get very graphic so if you can't handle it, don't read it. My philosophy was, if its good enough for Oprah, it's good enough for me.</span>
